{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idede50a55-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"74"},"text":"§ 74.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional findings and declaration of policy","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idede50a56-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Grain is an essential source of the world’s total supply of human food and animal feed and is merchandised in interstate and foreign commerce. It is declared to be the policy of the Congress, for the promotion and protection of such commerce in the interests of producers, merchandisers, warehousemen, processors, and consumers of grain, and the general welfare of the people of the United States, to provide for the establishment of official United States standards for grain, to promote the uniform application thereof by official inspection personnel, to provide for an official inspection system for grain, and to regulate the weighing and the certification of the weight of grain shipped in interstate or foreign commerce in the manner hereinafter provided; with the objectives that grain may be marketed in an orderly and timely manner and that trading in grain may be facilitated. It is hereby found that all grain and other articles and transactions in grain regulated under this chapter are either in interstate or foreign commerce or substantially affect such commerce and that regulation thereof as provided in this chapter is necessary to prevent or eliminate burdens on such commerce and to regulate effectively such commerce.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idede50a57-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" It is also declared to be the policy of Congress—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idede50a58-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to promote the marketing of grain of high quality to both domestic and foreign buyers;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idede50a59-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" that the primary objective of the official United States standards for grain is to certify the quality of grain as accurately as practicable; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idede50a5a-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" that official United States standards for grain shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idede50a5b-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/b/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" define uniform and accepted descriptive terms to facilitate trade in grain;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idede50a5c-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/b/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provide information to aid in determining grain storability;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idede50a5d-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/b/3/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" offer users of such standards the best possible information from which to determine end-product yield and quality of grain;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idede50a5e-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/b/3/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provide the framework necessary for markets to establish grain quality improvement incentives;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idede50a5f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/b/3/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" reflect the economic value-based characteristics in the end uses of grain; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idede50a60-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s74/b/3/F"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"F"},"text":"(F)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" accommodate scientific advances in testing and new knowledge concerning factors related to, or highly correlated with, the end use performance of grain.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idede50a61-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1916-08-11/ch313"},"text":"Aug. 11, 1916, ch. 313","children":[],"tail":", pt. B, § 2, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/39/482"},"text":"39 Stat. 482","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-07-18/ch636"},"text":"July 18, 1940, ch. 636","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/765"},"text":"54 Stat. 765","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/487/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–487, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1968-08-15"},"text":"Aug. 15, 1968","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/82/761"},"text":"82 Stat. 761","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/582/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–582, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2867"},"text":"90 Stat. 2867","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/641/tIII/s302"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–641, title III, § 302","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-10"},"text":"Nov. 10, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3564"},"text":"100 Stat. 3564","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/624/tXX/s2004"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–624, title XX, § 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-28"},"text":"Nov. 28, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/3929"},"text":"104 Stat. 3929","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idede50a62-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idede50a63-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idede50a64-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsec. (b)(3)(E), (F). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/624"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–624","children":[],"tail":" added subpars. (E) and (F)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/641"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–641","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as subsec. (a) and added subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1976—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/582"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–582","children":[],"tail":" expressed the policy of Congress to regulate the weighing and the certification of the weight of grain shipped in interstate or foreign commerce and the finding of Congress of the necessity to regulate grain transactions to prevent or eliminate burdens on commerce and to regulate effectively such interstate or foreign commerce, and provided that the grain be marketed in a timely manner."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1968—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/487"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–487","children":[],"tail":" substituted a declaration of policy by the Congress for provisions authorizing promulgation and establishment of grain standards by Secretary of Agriculture."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1940—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1940-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1940","children":[],"tail":", inserted “soybeans,” after “flaxseed,”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idede50a65-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"ef